Class SimpleSubmission<T>

  • Object
    • AbstractSubmission<T>
      • SimpleSubmission<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The expected type of the result of the submission.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Resettable, Submission<T>
    public class SimpleSubmission<T>
extends AbstractSubmission<T>
    A simple sub-class of the AbstractSubmission class that allows for the specification of the commands to execute and the result object to return.
    Author:
    Viktor Csomor

    • Constructor Detail

      • SimpleSubmission

        public SimpleSubmission​(List<Command> commands,
                        T result)
        Constructs a SimpleSubmission instance according to the specified parameters.
        Parameters:
        commands - A list of commands to execute. It should not contain null references.
        result - The result object that will be returned wrapped in an Optional when invoking the AbstractSubmission.getResult() method of the instance. Keeping the result a parameter of the submission allows for the commands of the submission to have a reference to the result object before instantiating this submission and therefore, it enables them to modify the result from their method definitions.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the commands are null or empty or contain at least one null reference.

      • SimpleSubmission

        public SimpleSubmission​(List<Command> commands)
        Constructs a SimpleSubmission instance according to the specified parameters. The submission's AbstractSubmission.getResult() method will always return an empty optional.
        Parameters:
        commands - A list of commands to execute. It should not contain null references.
        Throws:
